article.headline: VCU secures 87-78 win over Temple

images.name: Max Shulga makes a great defensive play for the steal
images.caption: Max Shulga makes a great defensive play for the steal

article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- — Zeb Jackson and Max Shulga both scored 19 points to help VCU defeat Temple 87-78 on Saturday. Jackson had six rebounds, seven assists, and four steals for the Rams (6-5). Shulga added six rebounds and five assists. Kuany Kuany was 4 of 7 shooting (2 for 3 from 3-point range) to finish with 12 points. Sam Hofman led the way for the Owls (6-4) with 17 points. Hysier Miller added 16 points and nine assists for Temple. In addition, Jahlil White finished with 14 points, 11 rebounds, four assists and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
